modules.description: Handles file uploads and downloads using HTTP protocols, supporting progress tracking and error handling. Operates with file paths, URLs, and binary data streams. Used to transfer large media files between a device and a server during app operations.

The module handles HTTP-based file uploads and downloads, including creating transfer objects, tracking progress, and managing errors. It operates on file paths, URLs, error objects, and custom options, alongside private JavaScript structures to enable structured file operations in web applications. Use cases include scenarios requiring reliable data transfer management, such as media uploads or resource downloads in mobile or web environments.
